<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Archegos oopsie</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A few years ago, Citigroup Inc. <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35524656.258330/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMTcvY2l0aS1jYW4=
tdC1oYXZlLWl0cy05MDAtbWlsbGlvbi1iYWNrP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA1MjgyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJn=
V0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDUyOCZ1d=
G1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc58ac08e" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
had an oopsie</a>=C2=A0where it accidentally wired $900 million to some hed=
ge funds. After giving it some thought, most of the hedge funds=C2=A0decide=
d to keep the money. Citi=C2=A0sued to get the money back and initially los=
t, though it <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35524=
656.258330/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjIt=
MDktMTIvY2l0aS1nb3QtaXRzLTUwMC1taWxsaW9uLWJhY2s_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDUyODI0X01PTkV=
ZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09Mj=
QwNTI4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa7d62a2c" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;">eventually won</a>. It was weird that Citi initially lost, and it wa=
s a little=C2=A0weird that the hedge funds even=C2=A0<em>tried </em>to keep=
 money that had been wired to them by accident. But they had an argument th=
at they deserved the money: They were in a fight with Revlon Inc. over some=
 covenants, and Citi was the administrative agent on their loan to Revlon=
=C2=A0and had accidentally sent the money on its behalf. And, you know, the=
re was the money, in their bank accounts. I wrote:</p><blockquote><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Aggressiveness and creativity are kind of the whole ba=
llgame when you are trading distressed debt; the business is about hunting =
for arcane advantages that you can exploit to get more money than the other=
 guys. In a sense the discharge-for-value exception is an arcane advantage,=
 but in another sense =E2=80=9Cwell they sent us money so we=E2=80=99re goi=
ng to keep it=E2=80=9D is the least arcane imaginable thing, and if you don=
=E2=80=99t have that instinct perhaps you were meant for a gentler corner o=
f the financial world.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And in =
fact Revlon did end up going bankrupt, so keeping the money was a good idea=
, though it ended up not working out.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That =
was about distressed-debt hedge funds and an odd doctrine of New York law, =
but I suppose the point is valid more generally.=C2=A0<em>Almost all of the=
 time</em>, in high finance, if you accidentally send a nine-digit sum of m=
oney to a counterparty, and then you call them up to say =E2=80=9Coops I di=
d not mean to send you those hundreds of millions of dollars, can I have th=
em back,=E2=80=9D they will say =E2=80=9Clol sure here you go, doofus,=E2=
=80=9D and you will both have a friendly laugh about it. Accidents happen. =
But!=C2=A0</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you have loaned mone=
y to a borrower who is now in distress and might not be able to pay you bac=
k, and</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">They send you the money by =
accident,</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Probably keep it?</li></=
ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is not=C2=A0<em>legal=C2=A0</em>advice=
, obviously, and in the Citi/Revlon case a court ultimately ruled against i=
t, but, you know. Sometimes you keep the money.=C2=A0Anyway, disclosure, I =
used to work at Goldman=C2=A0and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/35524656.258330/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2Fy=
dGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMjMvZ29sZG1hbi1taXN0YWtlbmx5LWdvdC00NzAtbWlsbGlvbi1mcm9=
tLWFyY2hlZ29zLWR1cmluZy1ibG93dXA_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDUyODI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX2=
1lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNTI4JnV0bV9jY=
W1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1328e3a5" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">I love t=
his</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As Archegos Capital Ma=
nagement was cratering in March 2021, it began trying to pull excess cash f=
rom trading accounts across Wall Street. At the time, it had about $470 mil=
lion with Goldman Sachs Group Inc.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But inst=
ead of withdrawing the money, an Archegos staffer accidentally wired that a=
mount to Goldman, and the bank didn=E2=80=99t immediately give it back. Tha=
t left Bill Hwang=E2=80=99s family office down nearly $1 billion as it was =
scrambling to prop up its positions and deal with the massive margin calls =
that would obliterate it days later. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">=E2=80=9CArchegos had approximately a billion dollars less in its opera=
ting account at Bank of America because of this error,=E2=80=9D [former Arc=
hegos risk chief Scott] Becker testified. Though Goldman initially indicate=
d it would return the money, a relationship manager at the bank wanted to t=
alk to Archegos head trader William Tomita first. That didn=E2=80=99t happe=
n, Becker said. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Goldman was one o=
f the banks able to offload its Archegos holdings relatively quickly, allow=
ing it to emerge unscathed from the debacle. Archegos=E2=80=99 largest coun=
terparty was Credit Suisse Group AG, and its $5.5 billion in losses trading=
 with Hwang contributed to its collapse last year.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p=
 style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">While Archegos <em>did=C2=A0</em>have that $470 =
million at Goldman, Goldman was also financing its positions, and by the ne=
xt day Goldman was sending it a $1.4 billion <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/35524656.258330/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNv=
bS9uZXdzL2xpdmUtYmxvZy8yMDI0LTA1LTI4L2FyY2hlZ29zLXRyaWFsLW1heS0yOD9jbXBpZD1=
CQkQwNTI4MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldH=
RlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA1MjgmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cB892bb4ae" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">margin call</a>. Did getting $470 million of extr=
a collateral<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-=
color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0by accident help Goldman emerge unscathed? It probably did not hu=
rt!</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile of course <a href=3D"https://=
link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35524656.258330/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb=
21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMjcvYmlsbC1od2FuZy1hcnJlc3Qt=
aW5zaWRlLXRoZS12aWNpb3VzLWN5Y2xlLW9mLWFyY2hlZ29zLWNvbGxhcHNlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA=
1MjgyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJn=
V0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDUyOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cB4c1f266b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;">Hwang is on trial</a> for allegedly defrauding the ban=
ks and manipulating the market, and I wonder which way this cuts. Hwang=E2=
=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35524656.2=
58330/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtM=
DcvYm9uZC1tYXJrZXRzLWFyZS10aGUtbmV3LXN0b2NrLW1hcmtldHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDUyODI0=
X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3R=
lcm09MjQwNTI4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBaac5=
4aff" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;">best defense</a> seems to me to be something like: =E2=80=9CN=
o, I wasn=E2=80=99t doing <em>market manipulation</em>; I just made a bunch=
 of reckless concentrated bets on stocks I like. And you can tell that I wa=
sn=E2=80=99t doing market manipulation because I didn=E2=80=99t make off wi=
th any money; every dollar of paper profits that I made on those bets was p=
lowed right back into those stocks.=E2=80=9D In some ways, =E2=80=9Cactuall=
y we tried to withdraw money from Goldman but we hit the wrong button=E2=80=
=9D undercuts that argument =E2=80=94=C2=A0maybe there=C2=A0<em>was=C2=A0</=
em>an exit strategy! =E2=80=94=C2=A0but I think mostly it strengthens it. T=
his certainly makes me more willing to believe that Archegos was reckless a=
nd didn=E2=80=99t have much of an exit plan.</p><table class=3D"liveintent-=
sponsored-content" width=3D"auto" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0">
