<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">In the olden days, insurance companies we=
re in the business of lending money to companies =E2=80=94=C2=A0by buying b=
onds =E2=80=94=C2=A0and holding the bonds to maturity.</li>=09<li style=3D"=
margin-bottom: 5px;">This was a sensible model for them, since they had loc=
ked-up customer money and long-term predictable=C2=A0liability schedules, s=
o they could easily hold the bonds to maturity.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-=
bottom: 5px;">Then Bill Gross invented the idea of trading bonds, which all=
owed insurance companies to make some excess returns (by selling overpriced=
