10px;">
<div id=3D"footnote-1" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[1] Or $940 million? If Archegos had sent the =
correct message =E2=80=94 asking to withdraw $470 million =E2=80=94 would G=
oldman have sent the money? My guess is no but I suppose it depends on the =
exact timing and how sweaty the request was.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-2" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[2] Again this is a very stylized model and I =
am kidding about things like Bill Gross *inventing* trading bonds, though t=
here=E2=80=99s a kernel of truth to it drawn from Mary Childs=E2=80=99s boo=
k <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35524656.258330/=
aHR0cDovL3d3dy5tYXJ5Y2hpbGRzLmNvbS90aGVib25ka2luZw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
Bd1c59c3d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">The Bond King</a>.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-3" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[3] Again, this is stylized, and of course pri=
vate credit funds raise money from lots of non-insurance limited partners. =
Still there is something to this. As the Wall Street Journal <a href=3D"htt=
ps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35524656.258330/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cu=
d3NqLmNvbS9maW5hbmNlL3ByaXZhdGUtbGVuZGVyLWJsdWUtb3dsLXB1c2hlcy1pbnRvLWluc3V=
yYW5jZS0xOWE1YTNmMD9tb2Q9aHBfbGVhZF9wb3MxMA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe5b000=
8c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">put it last month</a>: =E2=80=9CApollo Global Management spark=
ed Wall Street=E2=80=99s push into insurance when it helped create the insu=
rer Athene in the aftermath of the 2008-09 financial crisis and built a mas=
sive credit business to manage its assets. Other private-equity firms such =
as KKR, Blackstone and Brookfield have since bought insurers or struck deal=
s to manage their assets.=E2=80=9D Insurers, with their long-term money, ar=
e good customers for alternative asset managers; acquiring (or being acquir=
ed by) an insurer gives you first dibs on that money; but that money, being=
 insurance money, is probably looking for credit investments (rather than p=
rivate equity), so it pushes you into credit businesses.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-4" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[4] Of course there are other ways to think ab=
out it. Probably GameStop wouldn=E2=80=99t have done the offering at all at=
 pre-Roaring Kitty prices, which you can tell because it *didn=E2=80=99t* d=
o a stock offering until Gill tweeted. Also that $13.76 average price is a =
pretty arbitrary time period, and in the couple of weeks right before Gill=
=E2=80=99s tweet GameStop was trading lower.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-5" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[5] Arguably the answer is higher than $300 mi=
llion, because if you were *planning* this you=E2=80=99d have had the at-th=
e-market offering ready to go as soon as the tweets hit, and you=E2=80=99d =
have gotten a much better price than $20.74. The stock was at $48.75 on May=
 14, while they were drafting the paperwork!</p>
</div>
</td>
